20/11/2003
IZMIR, Turkey -- The NATO exercise Allied Forces '03 begins Thursday (20 November) at a training range south of Izmir. 
The exercise will demonstrate -- for the first time since Saturday's inauguration of the NATO Response Force -- the capabilities of the 11 member countries. 
A delegation from the Bulgarian Defence Ministry, led by Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov, will observe.
In other news, Sofia is hosting a Partnership for Peace exercise called Co-operative Associate A1-2. 
Commanders and staffs of NATO and partner nations will form a multinational brigade headquarters aimed at enhancing military interoperability. 
(Anadolu Agency, BTA, BNT, Nova TV - 19/11/03)
